            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/timestamps/AscendingTimestampExtractor.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextInputFormat.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/timestamps/AscendingTimestampExtractor.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"AscendingTimestampExtractor\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextInputFormat.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"TextInputFormat\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"apache/flink\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"TextOutputFormat\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"Found 3 deprecated classes in Apache Flink's DataStream API within the flink-streaming-java/src/ directory:\\n\\n1. **AscendingTimestampExtractor** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/functions/timestamps/AscendingTimestampExtractor.java, line 37): A timestamp assigner and watermark generator for streams where timestamps are monotonously ascending. This is a timestamp extractor class that is marked as @Deprecated. The class implements WatermarkStrategyWithPeriodicWatermarks<T> and provides methods for extracting timestamps and generating watermarks. While the deprecation javadoc does not explicitly state a replacement class name, the usage suggests migrating to the modern WatermarkStrategy API.\\n\\n2. **TextInputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextInputFormat.java, line 37): An I/O format class for reading text files where each line results in another element. The deprecation javadoc (lines 33-35) recommends: \\\"If you want to read/write data from/to text file, please use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink. This class should be removed if we drop the supports for read/write via input/output format in DataStream api.\\\" The replacement is FLIP-27 FileSource.\\n\\n3. **TextOutputFormat** (flink-streaming-java/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/legacy/io/TextOutputFormat.java, line 42): A FileOutputFormat subclass that writes objects to a text file. The deprecation javadoc (lines 37-40) recommends: \\\"If you want to read/write data from/to text file, please use FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink. This class should be removed if we drop all supports for InputFormat and OutputFormat\\\". The recommended replacements are FLIP-27 FileSource and Sink-V2 FlinkSink.\\n\\nAll three classes are I/O related components (one timestamp extractor and two I/O format classes) that represent the legacy API and should be replaced with newer FLIP-27 FileSource/Sink implementations or modern timestamp handling strategies.\"\n}\n",
